node.title: Five test positive to COVID-19 after boat cruise on Sydney Harbour, concerns two are Omicron variant
node.alt: The iconic white sails of the Sydney Opera House, lit up at night with lights shining out over the harbour water.
node.description: NSW Health is urgently contacting around 140 people who were on the boat and directing them and members of their households to immediately get tested, isolate and await further public advice.
node.content:
["NSW Health authorities have issued a public health alert\u00a0after a weekend party boat cruise on Sydney Harbour has seen five people test\u00a0positive for COVID-19 \u2014 with\u00a0two of those thought\u00a0likely to have the new Omicron strain of the virus.", "It says genome sequencing is underway to determine if any of the five confirmed cases have the Omicron variant.", "\"Preliminary results indicate two are likely to have it,\" a statement issued late on Tuesday night by NSW Health said.", "\"All cases are isolating at home.\"", "NSW Health is urgently contacting around 140 people who signed in with a QR code before boarding the boat and directing them and members of their households to immediately get tested, isolate and await further public advice.", "Operated by Cadman cruises, the party boat left King Street Wharf at 7.30pm, returning around 11pm.", "NSW Health says the cruise was jointly marketed as \"Flow Fridays \u2014 90s Themed Boat Party\"\u00a0and \"Freaky Sunday Afrovibe: The Last Dance\".", "Earlier health officials said a passenger on a flight from Doha to Sydney is believed to be the origin of the growing Omicron cluster in Sydney's west.", "The traveller arrived on 23\u00a0November after spending time in Nigeria.", "The so called Regents Park cluster has grown to 20 cases after six more were confirmed yesterday.", "So far nobody in New South Wales infected with the strain has been hospitalised.", "", "
Why we hear about some COVID-19 variants more than others
"]
